body:
In the new short story, the Curator&#039;s Gamble, there was this line:

_Januk was scowling. &ldquo;The Guild **aren&rsquo;t** particularly fond of you, Ezreal.&rdquo;_

Guild is a singular word, so it should be &quot;The Guild **isn&#039;t** particularly fond of you, Ezreal.&quot;

replies.body:
If it had been in narration, that could be a slightly different matter, of course. Assuming the narrator is not also a character speaking in their own particular, characterful way.

ART IS FUN! EXPRESSION IS SUBJECTIVE!

